<title>USA: SIGCORP votes 3-for-2 split, div increase.</title>
<headline>SIGCORP votes 3-for-2 split, div increase.</headline>
<dateline>EVANSVILLE, Ind. 1997-01-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>SIGCORP Inc said Tuesday its board had authorized a three-for-two stock split, payable March 27, record February 21.</p>
<p>Directors also approved a rise in the quarterly dividend to $0.4425 per pre-split share from $0.4325, payable March 20, record February 21.  </p>
<p>On a post-split basis, the dividend will amount to $0.295 a share.</p>
<p>SIGCORP, a holding company, through its public utility subsidiary SIGECO, is engaged in the generation, transmission, distribution and sale of electricity and the purchase of natural gas.</p>
<p>((-- Chicago Newsdesk 312 408-8787))</p>
